<font color="#FF0000">HEALING</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 30  9:08:02 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To build on Tom's post. Use this thread to act goofy and blow off.  There are places where this is not appropiate.  And I am the first one to admit it.<br>
To Ed, this is the site to do all those things that you want.  This is not the thread.  I sometimes forget that not all of us here have &quot;come home&quot; and still have issues to discuss.  Problems to work through and concerns to be put to rest.  I will offer my help if asked.  Sometimes even when not asked.  This is when my help becomes an opinion. My opinion! Not anyone elses.  Take it or leave it.  I assure you that it is never offered to challenge, hurt, control or mess with your head.  At least, intentionally.  As to the language.  When passionate feelings are being discussed it at times is difficult to use nouns where adjectives seem more appropiate.  It is hard to write in a format that does not reflect our rage and anger without using that language to get the point across. It is hard to offer these things without sounding pompous. And I am far from being &quot;cured&quot;.  But voices like mine and Art's and Doc Del's and Gerrey's and Tom's and yes, Doc Spatz, and all the other ones out there help process all those things that we haven't dealt with for so long.  It is tough to be over 50 years old and let things control your behavior that happened over 30 years ago.  But it is and it does.  So talk, listen, learn and heal.<br>
I apologize to all.  I needed to say that not just to Ed and to Cook but to myself as well.
